request.description:
## PATCH /property/{{newlyCreatedDropdownPropertyId}}

This endpoint allows you to update the properties of a dropdown in the system. Specifically, it modifies the options associated with a dropdown property identified by `{{newlyCreatedDropdownPropertyId}}`.

### Request Body

The request requires a JSON payload with the following structure:

``` json
{
  "options": {
    "labels": [
      {
        "title": "string",               // The title of the dropdown option
        "databasePropertyId": "string",  // The ID associated with the dropdown option in the database
        "position": "integer",            // The position of the option in the dropdown list
        "color": {
          "colorType": "string",         // Type of color used (e.g., palette)
          "payload": "integer"           // Identifier for the color
        }
      }
    ],
    "hasMultipleValues": "boolean",      // Indicates if multiple values can be selected
    "sortType": "string"                  // Defines the sorting type (e.g., manual)
  }
}

 ```

### Expected Input Parameters

- **options**: An object that contains:

    - **labels**: An array of label objects, each representing an option in the dropdown.

    - **hasMultipleValues**: A boolean indicating whether the dropdown allows multiple selections.

    - **sortType**: A string that specifies how the dropdown options should be sorted.


### Response Structure

The response will typically include the updated dropdown property details, which may mirror the structure of the request payload, confirming the changes made. The exact structure of the response may vary based on the implementation but will generally reflect the updated state of the dropdown property.

Ensure that the payload adheres to the specified structure to successfully update the dropdown options.

